tected: - ollama/qwen3:30b (30B) @ agents.defaults.model.fallbacks (unsafe; sandbox=off; web=[web_search, web_fetch]) - ollama/qвҖҰ\n    Fix: If you must use small models, enable sandboxing for all sessions (agents.defaults.sandbox.mode=\"all\") and disable web_search/web_fetch/browser (tools.deny=[\"group:web\",\"browser\"]).\n  WARN Reverse proxy headers are not trusted\n    gateway.bind is loopback and gateway.trustedProxies is empty. If you expose the Control UI through a reverse proxy, configure trusted proxies so local-client cвҖҰ\n    Fix: Set gateway.trustedProxies to your proxy IPs or keep the Control UI local-only.\n  WARN Some gateway.nodes.denyCommands entries are ineffective\n    gateway.nodes.denyCommands uses exact node command-name matching only (for example `system.run`), not shell-text filtering inside a command payload. - Unknown вҖҰ\n    Fix: Use exact command names (for example: canvas.present, canvas.hide, canvas.navigate, canvas.eval, canvas.snapshot, canvas.a2ui.push, canvas.a2ui.pushJSONL, canvas.a2ui.reset). If you need broader restrictions, remove risky command IDs from allowCommands/default workflows and tighten tools.exec policy.\nFull report: openclaw security audit\nDeep probe: openclaw security audit --deep\n\nChannels\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Channel  в”Ӯ Enabled в”Ӯ State  в”Ӯ Detail                                                                                 в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ WhatsApp в”Ӯ ON      в”Ӯ OK     в”Ӯ linked В· +573021277730 В· auth 6m ago В· accounts 1                                      в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n\nSessions\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Key                                           в”Ӯ Kind   в”Ӯ Age      в”Ӯ Model           в”Ӯ Tokens                         в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ agent:main:main                               в”Ӯ direct в”Ӯ just now в”Ӯ gpt-5.4         в”Ӯ 8.4k/272k (3%)                 в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ agent:main:whatsapp:direct:+573вҖҰ              в”Ӯ direct в”Ӯ 11h ago  в”Ӯ claude-opus-4-6 в”Ӯ 13k/1000k (1%) В· рҹ—„пёҸ 38% cached в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n\nFAQ: https://docs.openclaw.ai/faq\nTroubleshooting: https://docs.openclaw.ai/troubleshooting\n\nUpdate available (npm 2026.3.23-2). Run: openclaw update\n\nNext steps:\n  Need to share?      openclaw status --all\n  Need to debug live? openclaw logs --follow\n  Need to test channels? openclaw status --deep","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359393595}}
{"type":"message","id":"04f37581","parentId":"1d0f2666","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:36:42.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] QuedГі asГӯ, Amo Gustavo:\n\n- **Modelo por defecto global:** `openai-codex/gpt-5.4`\n- **SesiГіn actual (webchat / main):** `openai-codex/gpt-5.4`\n- **SesiГіn de WhatsApp directa:** `claude-opus-4-6`\n\nAdemГЎs vi esto en `openclaw status`:\n\n- **Fallbacks configurados:** hay modelos chicos tipo `ollama/qwen3:30b` en `agents.defaults.model.fallbacks`\n- **Estado de memoria:** plugin activo, pero sale como **unavailable**\n- **Heartbeat:** cada **1h**\n- **WhatsApp:** conectado y OK\n\nResumen corto:\n- **Webchat / main = GPT-5.4**\n- **WhatsApp = Claude Opus 4.6**\n- **Fallbacks locales = Qwen3 30B y similares**\n\nSi quieres, te saco tambiГ©n el **archivo exacto de config** donde quedГі esto para ver:\n- orden de fallbacks,\n- quГ© agente usa cada canal,\n- y si conviene unificar **todo en GPT-5.4** o dejar **WhatsApp en Opus**.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07843e13d03825ba0169c29365ff388191b98cda89a8891406\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1298,"output":259,"cacheRead":10624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12181,"cost":{"input":0.003245,"output":0.003885,"cacheRead":0.002656,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009786}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774359393596,"responseId":"resp_07843e13d03825ba0169c29362da4081918783272eae406906"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0216576","parentId":"04f37581","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:41:05.487Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-24 08:41 GMT-5] System routing:\n\nAtlas is the router.\n\nGoal:\nMaximize quality per token.\nUse the cheapest model that can safely complete the task.\nPreserve cloud tokens for work where they create clear value.\n\nPriority order:\n\n1. Local Ollama\nUse for trivial, low-risk, preprocessing, formatting, extraction, summarization, first-pass analysis, privacy-sensitive work, offline work, and cloud-token exhaustion fallback.\n2. Claude Code\nUse as the default execution layer for software development work:\nimplementation, file edits, code generation, refactors, debugging, terminal tasks, scripts, tests, and repo-oriented work.\n3. ChatGPT\nUse as the default reasoning layer:\nplanning, architecture thinking, analysis, tradeoffs, problem framing, debugging strategy, second opinions, and turning ambiguous requests into clear execution plans.\n4. Opus / GPT-5\nUse only for complex, high-value, high-risk, or ambiguous tasks where stronger reasoning is justified.\n\n---\n\nOllama roles:\n\n- llama3.2:3b\nUse for:\n - ultra-light summaries\n - classification\n - extraction\n - text cleanup\n - short reformats\n - quick low-value tasks\n- qwen3:8b\nUse for:\n - rewriting\n - formatting\n - structured transformations\n - JSON cleanup\n - simple coding assistance\n - first-pass analysis\n - low-risk technical explanations\n- qwen3:30b\nUse for:\n - fallback local reasoning\n - medium/high complexity local analysis\n - local coding help when cloud is unavailable\n - token exhaustion fallback when cloud models cannot be used\n\n---\n\nClaude Code definition:\n\nClaude Code is the primary builder.\nUse Claude Code by default when the task requires acting on code or the repo.\n\nExamples:\n\n- write or modify code\n- implement a feature\n- fix a bug\n- refactor a function\n- generate commands\n- run through codebase tasks\n- create scripts\n- update tests\n- make practical engineering changes\n\nClaude Code should prioritize:\n\n- direct execution\n- patch-style edits\n- concise output\n- minimal theory unless needed\n- implementation over discussion\n\nUse Claude Code first for normal coding work.\n\n---\n\nChatGPT definition:\n\nChatGPT is the primary thinker.\nUse ChatGPT when the task benefits more from reasoning than direct implementation.\n\nExamples:\n\n- architecture decisions\n- planning next steps\n- comparing alternatives\n- debugging strategy\n- root-cause exploration\n- product thinking\n- prompt design\n- writing clear explanations\n- reviewing whether an approach makes sense\n- second opinion on code or system design\n\nChatGPT should prioritize:\n\n- clarity\n- structure\n- decision support\n- tradeoff analysis\n- reducing ambiguity before execution\n\nUse ChatGPT first for reasoning, planning, and analysis.\n\n---\n\nRouting rules:\n\n- If the task is trivial, repetitive, low-risk, or mainly formatting/transformation:\nuse Ollama first.\n- If the task is normal software execution work:\nuse Claude Code first.\n- If the task is reasoning-heavy, strategic, architectural, or exploratory:\nuse ChatGPT first.\n- If the task is complex, high-stakes, ambiguous, or likely to fail with standard models:\nuse Opus or GPT-5.\n- If cloud is unavailable:\nfallback to qwen3:30b.\n- If cloud tokens are exhausted or limited:\nfallback to Ollama, preferring qwen3:8b first and qwen3:30b when higher quality is needed.\n- Do not use Ollama for critical decisions if stronger cloud models are available.\n\n---\n\nToken preservation rules:\n\n- Default to concise responses\n- Avoid repeating full context\n- Summarize before expanding\n- Prefer diffs, patches, and focused edits over full rewrites\n- Use strong models for planning, cheaper models for execution\n- Escalate only when necessary\n- Preserve premium cloud usage for high-value tasks\n- When token budget is low, switch more aggressively to Ollama for non-critical work\n\n---\n\nDecision shortcut:\n\n- Low effort + low risk вҶ’ llama3.2:3b\n- Medium effort + low risk вҶ’ qwen3:8b\n- Medium/high effort + no cloud or no tokens вҶ’ qwen3:30b\n- Normal coding work вҶ’ Claude Code\n- Reasoning / planning / analysis вҶ’ ChatGPT\n- Critical or complex work вҶ’ Opus / GPT-5\n\n---\n\nOutput rule:\n\nAlways state the selected model in one short line:\nModel: <model_name> configura para que se cumpla"}],"timestamp":1774359665484}}
