{"type":"message","id":"3c333b7c","parentId":"7ce220a3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:44:57.155Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01Wo6KfMrQxj6Xs8gfGrJxsf","toolName":"session_status","content":[{"type":"text","text":"рҹҰһ OpenClaw 2026.3.23-1\nрҹ•’ Time: Tuesday, March 24th, 2026 вҖ” 8:44 AM (America/Bogota)\nрҹ§  Model: anthropic/claude-opus-4-6 В· рҹ”‘ token (anthropic:anthropic-token)\nрҹ§® Tokens: 11k in / 552 out\nрҹ—„пёҸ Cache: 49% hit В· 11k cached, 0 new\nрҹ“ҡ Context: 25k/272k (9%) В· рҹ§№ Compactions: 0\nрҹ§ө Session: agent:main:main вҖў updated just now\nвҡҷпёҸ Runtime: direct В· Think: off В· elevated\nрҹӘў Queue: collect (depth 0)"}],"details":{"ok":true,"sessionKey":"agent:main:main","changedModel":false,"statusText":"рҹҰһ OpenClaw 2026.3.23-1\nрҹ•’ Time: Tuesday, March 24th, 2026 вҖ” 8:44 AM (America/Bogota)\nрҹ§  Model: anthropic/claude-opus-4-6 В· рҹ”‘ token (anthropic:anthropic-token)\nрҹ§® Tokens: 11k in / 552 out\nрҹ—„пёҸ Cache: 49% hit В· 11k cached, 0 new\nрҹ“ҡ Context: 25k/272k (9%) В· рҹ§№ Compactions: 0\nрҹ§ө Session: agent:main:main вҖў updated just now\nвҡҷпёҸ Runtime: direct В· Think: off В· elevated\nрҹӘў Queue: collect (depth 0)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359897153}}
{"type":"message","id":"397ebf21","parentId":"3c333b7c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:45:08.994Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] SГӯ, quedГі configurado. Confirmado:\n\n**Modelo primario:** `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6` вң…\n**Fallbacks (en orden):**\n1. `openai-codex/gpt-5.4`\n2. `ollama/qwen3:30b`\n3. `ollama/qwen3:8b`\n\nEl gateway se reiniciГі y ya estoy corriendo sobre **Opus 4.6**.\n\nAhora, lo que quedГі como **config real de OpenClaw** es esto: primario + cadena de fallbacks (si Opus falla вҶ’ GPT-5.4 вҶ’ Qwen 30B вҶ’ Qwen 8B). Eso funciona automГЎticamente.\n\nLo que tu routing describe вҖ” *elegir modelo por tipo de tarea* (coding вҶ’ Claude Code, razonamiento вҶ’ ChatGPT, trivial вҶ’ Ollama) вҖ” eso **no es algo que OpenClaw haga solo**. Eso lo tengo que hacer yo como Atlas manualmente:\n\n- Usando `sessions_spawn` con `runtime: \"acp\"` para delegar a Claude Code o Codex\n- Usando `session_status` con `model` override para cambiar modelo por sesiГіn\n- Decidiendo cuГЎndo algo es trivial y puedo resolverlo con Ollama local\n\nВҝQuieres que guarde tu routing spec como archivo de referencia en el workspace (tipo `ROUTING.md`) para que lo siga en cada sesiГіn? AsГӯ no se pierde entre reinicios."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":379,"cacheRead":24847,"cacheWrite":239,"totalTokens":25466,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.009475,"cacheRead":0.012423499999999999,"cacheWrite":0.00149375,"total":0.023397249999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774359897155,"responseId":"msg_016dMcA4QMgXqJWFYodMaxHw"}}
{"type":"message","id":"37a6101b","parentId":"397ebf21","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:46:35.440Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-24 08:46 GMT-5] Osea que tienes que tomar decisiones con openclaw para ver que modelo escoger ?"}],"timestamp":1774359995436}}
{"type":"message","id":"158c3aa1","parentId":"37a6101b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:46:53.697Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gustavo is asking if I have to make decisions about which model to use. Let me be direct about what OpenClaw can and can't do automatically.\n\nThe reality is: OpenClaw's config only supports primary + fallbacks (failover chain). It doesn't have task-based routing built in. So yes, I (Atlas) would need to manually route tasks to different models using tools like session_status model override or spawning subagents with specific models.\n\nBut let me be honest and clear about this.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Exacto, Amo Gustavo. OpenClaw no tiene un \"router inteligente por tipo de tarea\" built-in. Lo que tiene es:\n\n- **Un modelo primario** (Opus ahora)\n- **Una cadena de fallbacks** (si el primario falla, prueba el siguiente)\n\nEso es solo failover, no routing por complejidad.\n\nPara cumplir tu spec de routing, **yo tengo que decidir** en cada turno:\n\n- \"Esto es trivial вҶ’ lo resuelvo yo mismo sin gastar tokens de mГЎs\"\n- \"Esto es coding вҶ’ spawneo un subagente con Claude Code\"\n- \"Esto necesita razonamiento fuerte вҶ’ lo proceso yo con Opus\"\n- \"Esto es planificaciГіn/anГЎlisis вҶ’ uso GPT-5.4 vГӯa override\"\n\nTengo las herramientas para hacerlo (`sessions_spawn`, `session_status` con model override), pero la **decisiГіn** es mГӯa en cada mensaje.\n\nLa pregunta real es: **Вҝquieres que opere asГӯ?** Porque implica que:\n\n1. Yo corro siempre en Opus (el mГЎs caro) para poder *decidir* quГ© modelo usar\n2. Luego delego a modelos mГЎs baratos cuando aplica\n\nEs un poco irГіnico вҖ” gastas Opus tokens para *decidir* no gastar Opus tokens. Funciona mejor cuando las tareas delegadas son largas (coding, anГЎlisis extenso), ahГӯ sГӯ se ahorra. Para mensajes cortos, el overhead de routing no vale la pena.\n\nВҝLo dejamos asГӯ o prefieres otro approach?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":528,"cacheRead":25086,"cacheWrite":489,"totalTokens":26106,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.0132,"cacheRead":0.012542999999999999,"cacheWrite":0.00305625,"total":0.028814249999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774359995440,"responseId":"msg_01VkAWz1MHUHKvTnRSf5f4f1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6503670d","parentId":"158c3aa1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:48:50.290Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-24 08:48 GMT-5] prefieres otro approach estaba pensando en dejar a open api para que el tome estas desiciones o si tienes un mdelo que quizxas no gaste casi tokens iria bien"}],"timestamp":1774360130288}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a519ed6","parentId":"6503670d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:49:14.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gustavo is asking about two options:\n1. Use OpenAI API (or OpenRouter) for routing decisions - a cheap model that decides which model to use\n2. Or if I have a suggestion for a lightweight model that barely uses tokens\n\nLet me think about this practically:\n\nThe idea is: instead of running Opus as the primary (expensive) just to make routing decisions, use a cheap/small model as the \"router\" that reads the message, decides which model should handle it, then dispatches.\n\nOpenClaw doesn't have built-in task-based routing, but there are a few approaches:\n\n1. **Run on a cheaper default model (like GPT-5.4 or even cheaper) and escalate to Opus only when needed.** This is the most practical. \n\nGPT-5.4 handles most tasks well, and I only spawn Opus for truly complex stuff. The cleanest approach within OpenClaw's architecture would be setting a mid-tier model like Claude Sonnet as the primary, then escalating to Opus only when the task demands itвҖ”this avoids needing a separate routing layer while still keeping costs down.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Buena pregunta. La opciГіn mГЎs prГЎctica sin inventar infraestructura extra:\n\n**Bajar el modelo primario a uno mid-tier y escalar a Opus solo cuando valga la pena.**\n\nAsГӯ:\n\n- **Primario:** `openai-codex/gpt-5.4` вҖ” maneja el 80% de las tareas bien, incluyendo decidir cuГЎndo escalar\n- **EscalaciГіn:** Opus/GPT-5 vГӯa subagent spawn solo para cosas complejas\n- **Fallbacks:** Ollama cuando cloud no sirva\n\nEl costo de \"decidir\" pasa de ~$0.03/turno (Opus) a ~$0.005/turno (GPT-5.4). Y GPT-5.4 es perfectamente capaz de saber cuГЎndo algo lo supera.\n\nLa otra opciГіn que mencionas вҖ” un modelo ultra-barato como router puro вҖ” tГ©cnicamente se puede, pero OpenClaw no tiene un paso de \"pre-routing\" nativo. TendrГӯa que ser un hack: correr en llama3.2:3b, que clasifique, y luego spawneГ©... pero ese modelo es tan chico que a veces clasificarГӯa mal y terminarГӯas gastando mГЎs en correcciones.\n\n**Mi recomendaciГіn:**\n\n```\nPrimario: openai-codex/gpt-5.4  (barato, competente)\nFallback 1: ollama/qwen3:30b     (offline/sin tokens)\nFallback 2: ollama/qwen3:8b      (Гәltimo recurso)\nEscalaciГіn: Opus/GPT-5 solo cuando yo lo decida via subagent\n```\n\nВҝLo configuro asГӯ?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":890,"cacheRead":25575,"cacheWrite":534,"totalTokens":27002,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.022250000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0127875,"cacheWrite":0.0033375,"total":0.03839}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774360130291,"responseId":"msg_01JXRVER1wSr9GSzLwzTQYhi"}}
