{"type":"message","id":"47587955","parentId":"4eb1f8d5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:03:30.466Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kuCDzLdMIP8XmCmmSte2PBwT|fc_07843e13d03825ba0169c299b28a6481919fbc1d8f0a611f0d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cmd /c openclaw config --help","workdir":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"cmd /c openclaw config --help\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":30}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":717,"output":52,"cacheRead":22272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23041,"cost":{"input":0.0017925,"output":0.00078,"cacheRead":0.005568,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0081405}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774361002937,"responseId":"resp_07843e13d03825ba0169c299ac8d648191a63077404394149c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b7e1e5a4","parentId":"47587955","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:03:31.009Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_kuCDzLdMIP8XmCmmSte2PBwT|fc_07843e13d03825ba0169c299b28a6481919fbc1d8f0a611f0d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"рҹҰһ OpenClaw 2026.3.23-1 (unknown) вҖ” Hot reload for config, cold sweat for deploys.\n\nUsage: openclaw config [options] [command]\n\nNon-interactive config helpers (get/set/unset/file/validate). Run without\nsubcommand for guided setup.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --section <section>  Configuration sections for guided setup (repeatable). Use\n                       with no subcommand. (default: [])\n\nCommands:\n  file                 Print the active config file path\n  get                  Get a config value by dot path\n  set                  Set config values by path (value mode, ref/provider\n                       builder mode, or batch JSON mode).\n                       Examples:\n                       openclaw config set gateway.port 19001 --strict-json\n                       openclaw config set channels.discord.token --ref-provider\n                       default --ref-source env --ref-id DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\n                       openclaw config set secrets.providers.vault\n                       --provider-source file --provider-path\n                       /etc/openclaw/secrets.json --provider-mode json\n                       openclaw config set --batch-file ./config-set.batch.json\n                       --dry-run\n  unset                Remove a config value by dot path\n  validate             Validate the current config against the schema without\n                       starting the gateway\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/config"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":532,"aggregated":"рҹҰһ OpenClaw 2026.3.23-1 (unknown) вҖ” Hot reload for config, cold sweat for deploys.\n\nUsage: openclaw config [options] [command]\n\nNon-interactive config helpers (get/set/unset/file/validate). Run without\nsubcommand for guided setup.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --section <section>  Configuration sections for guided setup (repeatable). Use\n                       with no subcommand. (default: [])\n\nCommands:\n  file                 Print the active config file path\n  get                  Get a config value by dot path\n  set                  Set config values by path (value mode, ref/provider\n                       builder mode, or batch JSON mode).\n                       Examples:\n                       openclaw config set gateway.port 19001 --strict-json\n                       openclaw config set channels.discord.token --ref-provider\n                       default --ref-source env --ref-id DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\n                       openclaw config set secrets.providers.vault\n                       --provider-source file --provider-path\n                       /etc/openclaw/secrets.json --provider-mode json\n                       openclaw config set --batch-file ./config-set.batch.json\n                       --dry-run\n  unset                Remove a config value by dot path\n  validate             Validate the current config against the schema without\n                       starting the gateway\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/config","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361011007}}
{"type":"message","id":"35551659","parentId":"b7e1e5a4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:03:46.506Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] SГӯ, **se puede**, pero no vi una opciГіn nativa tipo вҖңauto-restart on config setвҖқ en OpenClaw.\n\nLo que sГӯ se puede hacer es dejarte un **wrapper** o alias que haga:\n\n1. cambia config  \n2. valida  \n3. reinicia gateway  \n4. opcional: reabra/refresh del TUI\n\nEjemplo de idea:\n\n- `oc-model-set primary openai-codex/gpt-5.4`\n- internamente hace:\n  - `openclaw config set ...`\n  - `openclaw config validate`\n  - `openclaw gateway restart`\n\n**En corto:**\n- **Nativo automГЎtico, no lo vi**\n- **Automatizable con script, sГӯ totalmente**\n\nMi recomendaciГіn es esa, porque es mГЎs segura que reiniciar el gateway ante **cualquier** cambio de config.\n\nSi quieres, te lo dejo hecho como un `.cmd` o `.ps1` en tu workspace para aplicar cambios de modelo con reinicio automГЎtico.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07843e13d03825ba0169c299befe548191946373e1e42cbe92\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":433,"output":218,"cacheRead":22912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23563,"cost":{"input":0.0010825000000000001,"output":0.00327,"cacheRead":0.005728,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0100805}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774361011010,"responseId":"resp_07843e13d03825ba0169c299b7e3e0819188c439e5205709d8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"370d7a44","parentId":"35551659","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:06:32.465Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-24 09:06 GMT-5] Si es que me preocupa que por algun cambio se cierre el gateway y me quede sin servicio"}],"timestamp":1774361192462}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f4cc2aa","parentId":"370d7a44","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:06:43.358Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] SГӯ, esa preocupaciГіn es vГЎlida.\n\nSi lo haces **automГЎtico para todo**, te expones a esto:\n\n- guardas un cambio medio roto\n- el script reinicia igual\n- el gateway no levanta bien\n- y te quedas sin servicio hasta corregirlo manualmente\n\nO peor:\n- reinicia mientras WhatsApp/TUI estГЎn en uso\n- corta sesiones activas\n- genera confusiГіn aunque luego vuelva\n\nEntonces yo **no** pondrГӯa вҖңauto-restart siempreвҖқ a cualquier cambio.\n\n**Mejor approach: reinicio seguro, no reinicio ciego.**\n\nFlujo recomendado:\n\n1. **escribir config**\n2. **validar config**\n3. **solo si valida, reiniciar**\n4. **verificar health/status despuГ©s**\n5. si falla, **avisar y no seguir**\n\nO sea, algo tipo:\n\n- `set config`\n- `openclaw config validate`\n- `openclaw gateway restart`\n- `openclaw status`\n\nY solo marcar Г©xito si al final el gateway quedГі **reachable**.\n\n**Mi recomendaciГіn concreta:**\n\n- **No auto-restart global**\n- **SГӯ comando seguro para cambios sensibles**\n- **Y backup automГЎtico antes de tocar config**  \n  (igual OpenClaw ya deja `.bak`, eso ayuda bastante)\n\nEn resumen:\n- **AutomГЎtico total:** cГіmodo, pero riesgoso\n- **AutomГЎtico con validaciГіn + health check:** sГӯ vale la pena\n- **Manual puro:** mГЎs seguro, pero mГЎs molesto\n\nSi quieres, te preparo un pequeГұo script вҖңsafe-apply-configвҖқ que:\n- haga backup\n- valide\n- reinicie\n- confirme que el gateway volviГі\n- y si no, te diga exactamente quГ© fallГі\n\nEse sГӯ me parece buen equilibrio.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07843e13d03825ba0169c29a6afa54819184a4b0d3ef9d52de\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":237,"output":375,"cacheRead":23424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24036,"cost":{"input":0.0005925,"output":0.005625,"cacheRead":0.005856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012073500000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774361192466,"responseId":"resp_07843e13d03825ba0169c29a69e5388191a5ab42513fb0dd1e"}}
