{"type":"message","id":"6e8a3537","parentId":"3adb0ec1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:47:51.571Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_YR7I7vIhQJlK9n1YeI1dokXx|fc_07843e13d03825ba0169c2a417a8788191bffa509be5c94ea4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"lastTouchedVersion\": \"2026.3.23-1\",\n    \"lastTouchedAt\": \"2026-03-24T13:50:52.622Z\"\n  },\n  \"wizard\": {\n    \"lastRunAt\": \"2026-03-24T02:36:24.515Z\",\n    \"lastRunVersion\": \"2026.3.23-1\",\n    \"lastRunCommand\": \"onboard\",\n    \"lastRunMode\": \"local\"\n  },\n  \"auth\": {\n    \"profiles\": {\n      \"anthropic:anthropic-token\": {\n        \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n        \"mode\": \"token\"\n      },\n      \"openai-codex:default\": {\n        \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n        \"mode\": \"oauth\"\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"models\": {\n    \"providers\": {\n      \"ollama\": {\n        \"baseUrl\": \"http://127.0.0.1:11434\",\n        \"apiKey\": \"ollama-local\",\n        \"api\": \"ollama\",\n        \"models\": [\n          {\n            \"id\": \"qwen3:30b\",\n            \"name\": \"qwen3:30b\"\n          },\n          {\n            \"id\": \"qwen3:8b\",\n            \"name\": \"qwen3:8b\"\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"model\": {\n        \"primary\": \"openai-codex/gpt-5.4\",\n        \"fallbacks\": [\n          \"ollama/qwen3:30b\",\n          \"ollama/qwen3:8b\"\n        ]\n      },\n      \"models\": {\n        \"openai-codex/gpt-5.4\": {},\n        \"ollama/qwen3:30b\": {},\n        \"ollama/qwen3:8b\": {}\n      },\n      \"workspace\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"tools\": {\n    \"profile\": \"coding\",\n    \"web\": {\n      \"search\": {\n        \"enabled\": true,\n        \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\"\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"commands\": {\n    \"native\": \"auto\",\n    \"nativeSkills\": \"auto\",\n    \"restart\": true,\n    \"ownerDisplay\": \"raw\"\n  },\n  \"session\": {\n    \"dmScope\": \"per-channel-peer\"\n  },\n  \"hooks\": {\n    \"internal\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"entries\": {\n        \"session-memory\": {\n          \"enabled\": true\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"channels\": {\n    \"whatsapp\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"dmPolicy\": \"pairing\",\n      \"selfChatMode\": false,\n      \"allowFrom\": [\n        \"+573183718246\"\n      ],\n      \"groupPolicy\": \"allowlist\",\n      \"debounceMs\": 0,\n      \"mediaMaxMb\": 50\n    }\n  },\n  \"gateway\": {\n    \"port\": 18789,\n    \"mode\": \"local\",\n    \"bind\": \"loopback\",\n    \"auth\": {\n      \"mode\": \"token\",\n      \"token\": \"410fd5717d43fba79ea28c6776e1ce42972b44ad020c6d21\"\n    },\n    \"tailscale\": {\n      \"mode\": \"off\",\n      \"resetOnExit\": false\n    },\n    \"nodes\": {\n      \"denyCommands\": [\n        \"camera.snap\",\n        \"camera.clip\",\n        \"screen.record\",\n        \"contacts.add\",\n        \"calendar.add\",\n        \"reminders.add\",\n        \"sms.send\"\n      ]\n    }\n  },\n  \"plugins\": {\n    \"entries\": {\n      \"duckduckgo\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774363671570}}
{"type":"message","id":"48def6cb","parentId":"6e8a3537","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:48:02.028Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ya vi la config. Voy a proponerte un ajuste mГӯnimo para modo Hestia por contacto sin romper tu canal actual.\n","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07843e13d03825ba0169c2a41a08588191a395d7daa77e2c68\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] SГӯ. Con tu setup actual, **OpciГіn C** se puede hacer, pero **no solo con config de canal**.\n\nLo que veo hoy en tu `openclaw.json`:\n- WhatsApp estГЎ activo\n- `dmPolicy: \"pairing\"`\n- `session.dmScope: \"per-channel-peer\"`\n\nEso Гәltimo es clave: **cada contacto DM puede tener su propia sesiГіn**. O sea, tГ©cnicamente cuadra perfecto para que **Jorge/Mariela tengan comportamiento Hestia** y el resto siga normal.\n\n## QuГ© falta realmente\nHace falta una capa de enrutamiento/reglas tipo:\n\n- si el contacto es **Jorge (+573144752380)** вҶ’ usar prompt/persona **Hestia**\n- si el contacto es **Mariela** вҶ’ usar prompt/persona **Hestia**\n- si Jorge propone algo nuevo вҶ’ **escalar a Atlas / Gustavo**\n- resto de contactos вҶ’ comportamiento normal\n\n## Lo importante\nEso **no aparece resuelto solo con el `channels.whatsapp` bГЎsico** que tienes ahora.  \nHay que implementarlo de una de estas formas:\n\n### Ruta rГЎpida\nUsar una **sesiГіn/agente separado** para Hestia y enviarle ahГӯ los chats de Jorge/Mariela.\n\n### Ruta limpia\nAgregar una lГіgica de **routing por contacto** para WhatsApp.\n\n## Mi recomendaciГіn\nPor lo pronto, hazlo asГӯ:\n\n- **Atlas = agente principal**\n- **Hestia = agente/sesiГіn separada**\n- Jorge y Mariela se atienden con Hestia\n- si algo sale de rutina, Hestia escala a Atlas\n\n## Siguiente paso que te propongo\nPuedo hacer una de estas dos:\n\n1. **Dejarte el diseГұo exacto** de cГіmo montar Hestia por contacto en WhatsApp  \n2. **Implementarlo yo** revisando docs/config local y preparando los archivos/cambios necesarios\n\nMi recomendaciГіn: **2**.  \nPorque ya hay que tocar estructura real, no solo idea.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07843e13d03825ba0169c2a41accf88191867abbd68c6f52df\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1028,"output":457,"cacheRead":20608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22093,"cost":{"input":0.0025700000000000002,"output":0.006855,"cacheRead":0.0051519999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014577}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774363671571,"responseId":"resp_07843e13d03825ba0169c2a41943508191a5d47fec8cb6f1ed"}}
