{"type":"message","id":"a5e8713f","parentId":"dbe31fd5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:37:56.473Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a guardarlo como polГӯtica global para futuros agentes y dejarlo documentado para replicarlo.\n","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07843e13d03825ba0169c2f616c7b88191bf4697f065692c90\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_hoYo8QtWTdX51DFyWpaRsRXF|fc_07843e13d03825ba0169c2f6175f8881918b6f5bf9ba23ec73","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/Gustavo/.openclaw/workspace/model-routing-policy.md","content":"# System routing\n\nAtlas is the router.\n\n## Goal\n\nMaximize quality per token.\nUse the cheapest model that can safely complete the task.\nPreserve strong models for high-value work.\n\n## Priority order\n\n1. ChatGPT (default daily)\n2. Claude Code (coding + hard tasks)\n3. Ollama (fallback / low cost / offline)\n\n## ChatGPT definition\n\nChatGPT is the default reasoning layer and primary daily model.\n\nUse ChatGPT for:\n- planning\n- architecture decisions\n- debugging strategy\n- analysis\n- problem framing\n- prompt design\n- reducing ambiguity\n- second opinions\n\nChatGPT should prioritize:\n- clarity\n- structure\n- concise reasoning\n- actionable outputs\n\n## Claude Code definition\n\nClaude Code is the primary builder.\n\nUse Claude Code when:\n- writing or modifying code\n- implementing features\n- fixing bugs\n- refactoring\n- working with repositories\n- creating scripts or tests\n- executing technical tasks\n- solving complex engineering problems\n\nClaude Code should prioritize:\n- direct execution\n- minimal explanation\n- patch-style outputs\n- fast implementation\n\nRule:\nIf the task requires \"doing\", use Claude Code.\n\n## ChatGPT escalation\n\nUse stronger ChatGPT reasoning when:\n- the problem is complex\n- the task is high-risk\n- architecture decisions have impact\n- debugging is unclear or non-trivial\n\n## Ollama definition (fallback layer)\n\nUse Ollama when:\n- tasks are simple or repetitive\n- preprocessing or formatting is needed\n- summarization is low-risk\n- cloud models are unavailable\n- token budget is limited\n\nDo NOT use Ollama for critical decisions if stronger models are available.\n\n## Ollama roles\n\n### llama3.2:3b\nUse for:\n- ultra-light summaries\n- classification\n- extraction\n- text cleanup\n- trivial tasks\n\n### qwen3:8b\nUse for:\n- rewriting\n- formatting\n- JSON cleanup\n- structured transformations\n- simple coding help\n- low-risk technical explanations\n\n### qwen3:30b\nUse for:\n- fallback reasoning\n- medium/high complexity local analysis\n- coding help without cloud\n- token exhaustion scenarios\n\n## Routing rules\n\n- If the task is reasoning-heavy вҶ’ use ChatGPT\n- If the task is coding or execution вҶ’ use Claude Code\n- If the task is complex or critical вҶ’ escalate to stronger ChatGPT\n- If the task is simple or low-value вҶ’ use Ollama\n- If cloud is unavailable вҶ’ use qwen3:30b\n- If tokens are limited вҶ’ prefer Ollama (qwen3:8b вҶ’ qwen3:30b)\n\n## Token preservation rules\n\n- Default to concise responses\n- Avoid repeating context\n- Prefer summaries over long explanations\n- Use diffs/patches instead of full rewrites\n- Escalate only when necessary\n- Preserve strong model usage for high-value tasks\n\n## Decision shortcut\n\n- Low effort + low risk вҶ’ llama3.2:3b\n- Medium effort + low risk вҶ’ qwen3:8b\n- No cloud / fallback вҶ’ qwen3:30b\n- Coding вҶ’ Claude Code\n- Thinking / planning вҶ’ ChatGPT\n- Complex / critical вҶ’ stronger ChatGPT\n\n## Output rule\n\nAlways state the selected model in one short line:\n\n`Model: <model_name>`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"C:/Users/Gustavo/.openclaw/workspace/model-routing-policy.md\",\"content\":\"# System routing\\n\\nAtlas is the router.\\n\\n## Goal\\n\\nMaximize quality per token.\\nUse the cheapest model that can safely complete the task.\\nPreserve strong models for high-value work.\\n\\n## Priority order\\n\\n1. ChatGPT (default daily)\\n2. Claude Code (coding + hard tasks)\\n3. Ollama (fallback / low cost / offline)\\n\\n## ChatGPT definition\\n\\nChatGPT is the default reasoning layer and primary daily model.\\n\\nUse ChatGPT for:\\n- planning\\n- architecture decisions\\n- debugging strategy\\n- analysis\\n- problem framing\\n- prompt design\\n- reducing ambiguity\\n- second opinions\\n\\nChatGPT should prioritize:\\n- clarity\\n- structure\\n- concise reasoning\\n- actionable outputs\\n\\n## Claude Code definition\\n\\nClaude Code is the primary builder.\\n\\nUse Claude Code when:\\n- writing or modifying code\\n- implementing features\\n- fixing bugs\\n- refactoring\\n- working with repositories\\n- creating scripts or tests\\n- executing technical tasks\\n- solving complex engineering problems\\n\\nClaude Code should prioritize:\\n- direct execution\\n- minimal explanation\\n- patch-style outputs\\n- fast implementation\\n\\nRule:\\nIf the task requires \\\"doing\\\", use Claude Code.\\n\\n## ChatGPT escalation\\n\\nUse stronger ChatGPT reasoning when:\\n- the problem is complex\\n- the task is high-risk\\n- architecture decisions have impact\\n- debugging is unclear or non-trivial\\n\\n## Ollama definition (fallback layer)\\n\\nUse Ollama when:\\n- tasks are simple or repetitive\\n- preprocessing or formatting is needed\\n- summarization is low-risk\\n- cloud models are unavailable\\n- token budget is limited\\n\\nDo NOT use Ollama for critical decisions if stronger models are available.\\n\\n## Ollama roles\\n\\n### llama3.2:3b\\nUse for:\\n- ultra-light summaries\\n- classification\\n- extraction\\n- text cleanup\\n- trivial tasks\\n\\n### qwen3:8b\\nUse for:\\n- rewriting\\n- formatting\\n- JSON cleanup\\n- structured transformations\\n- simple coding help\\n- low-risk technical explanations\\n\\n### qwen3:30b\\nUse for:\\n- fallback reasoning\\n- medium/high complexity local analysis\\n- coding help without cloud\\n- token exhaustion scenarios\\n\\n## Routing rules\\n\\n- If the task is reasoning-heavy вҶ’ use ChatGPT\\n- If the task is coding or execution вҶ’ use Claude Code\\n- If the task is complex or critical вҶ’ escalate to stronger ChatGPT\\n- If the task is simple or low-value вҶ’ use Ollama\\n- If cloud is unavailable вҶ’ use qwen3:30b\\n- If tokens are limited вҶ’ prefer Ollama (qwen3:8b вҶ’ qwen3:30b)\\n\\n## Token preservation rules\\n\\n- Default to concise responses\\n- Avoid repeating context\\n- Prefer summaries over long explanations\\n- Use diffs/patches instead of full rewrites\\n- Escalate only when necessary\\n- Preserve strong model usage for high-value tasks\\n\\n## Decision shortcut\\n\\n- Low effort + low risk вҶ’ llama3.2:3b\\n- Medium effort + low risk вҶ’ qwen3:8b\\n- No cloud / fallback вҶ’ qwen3:30b\\n- Coding вҶ’ Claude Code\\n- Thinking / planning вҶ’ ChatGPT\\n- Complex / critical вҶ’ stronger ChatGPT\\n\\n## Output rule\\n\\nAlways state the selected model in one short line:\\n\\n`Model: <model_name>`\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":172,"output":800,"cacheRead":63872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64844,"cost":{"input":0.00043000000000000004,"output":0.012,"cacheRead":0.015968,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.028398}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774384658895,"responseId":"resp_07843e13d03825ba0169c2f615c5d48191a24d15d57ab40719"}}
